.TH "bitmap_allocate_region" 9 "bitmap_allocate_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bitmap_allocate_region \- allocate bitmap region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bitmap_allocate_region
.BI "(unsigned long *bitmap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pos "  ","
.BI "int order "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bitmap" 12
array of unsigned longs corresponding to the bitmap
.IP "pos" 12
beginning of bit region to allocate
.IP "order" 12
region size (log base 2 of number of bits) to allocate
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate (set bits in) a specified region of a bitmap.

Return 0 on success, or -EBUSY if specified region wasn't
free (not all bits were zero).
